{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":899,"text":"Intelligence -- what is it?"},{"time":4566,"text":"If we take a look back at the history"},{"time":6857,"text":"of how intelligence has been viewed,"},{"time":9481,"text":"one seminal example has been"},{"time":13099,"text":"Edsger Dijkstra's famous quote that"},{"time":16576,"text":"\"the question of whether a machine can think"},{"time":19687,"text":"is about as interesting"},{"time":20997,"text":"as the question of whether a submarine"},{"time":23968,"text":"can swim.\""},{"time":25758,"text":"Now, Edsger Dijkstra, when he wrote this,"},{"time":29602,"text":"intended it as a criticism"},{"time":31656,"text":"of the early pioneers of computer science,"},{"time":34656,"text":"like Alan Turing."},{"time":36403,"text":"However, if you take a look back"},{"time":38902,"text":"and think about what have been"},{"time":40867,"text":"the most empowering innovations"},{"time":42863,"text":"that enabled us to build"},{"time":44742,"text":"artificial machines that swim"},{"time":46976,"text":"and artificial machines that [fly],"},{"time":49549,"text":"you find that it was only through understanding"},{"time":53096,"text":"the underlying physical mechanisms"},{"time":55704,"text":"of swimming and flight"},{"time":58483,"text":"that we were able to build these machines."},{"time":61655,"text":"And so, several years ago,"},{"time":63911,"text":"I undertook a program to try to understand"},{"time":67160,"text":"the fundamental physical mechanisms"},{"time":69794,"text":"underlying intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72562,"text":"Let's take a step back."},{"time":74422,"text":"Let's first begin with a thought experiment."},{"time":77571,"text":"Pretend that you're an alien race"},{"time":80425,"text":"that doesn't know anything about Earth biology"},{"time":83466,"text":"or Earth neuroscience or Earth intelligence,"},{"time":86582,"text":"but you have amazing telescopes"},{"time":88774,"text":"and you're able to watch the Earth,"},{"time":91136,"text":"and you have amazingly long lives,"},{"time":93468,"text":"so you're able to watch the Earth"},{"time":94967,"text":"over millions, even billions of years."},{"time":98409,"text":"And you observe a really strange effect."},{"time":101424,"text":"You observe that, over the course of the millennia,"},{"time":105736,"text":"Earth is continually bombarded with asteroids"},{"time":110021,"text":"up until a point,"},{"time":112108,"text":"and that at some point,"},{"time":113639,"text":"corresponding roughly to our year, 2000 AD,"},{"time":117831,"text":"asteroids that are on"},{"time":119547,"text":"a collision course with the Earth"},{"time":121478,"text":"that otherwise would have collided"},{"time":123453,"text":"mysteriously get deflected"},{"time":125868,"text":"or they detonate before they can hit the Earth."},{"time":128940,"text":"Now of course, as earthlings,"},{"time":131023,"text":"we know the reason would be"},{"time":132567,"text":"that we're trying to save ourselves."},{"time":134323,"text":"We're trying to prevent an impact."},{"time":137403,"text":"But if you're an alien race"},{"time":139114,"text":"who doesn't know any of this,"},{"time":140260,"text":"doesn't have any concept of Earth intelligence,"},{"time":142774,"text":"you'd be forced to put together"},{"time":144502,"text":"a physical theory that explains how,"},{"time":147420,"text":"up until a certain point in time,"},{"time":149958,"text":"asteroids that would demolish the surface of a planet"},{"time":154407,"text":"mysteriously stop doing that."},{"time":157638,"text":"And so I claim that this is the same question"},{"time":161842,"text":"as understanding the physical nature of intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165840,"text":"So in this program that I\nundertook several years ago,"},{"time":169722,"text":"I looked at a variety of different threads"},{"time":172487,"text":"across science, across a variety of disciplines,"},{"time":175649,"text":"that were pointing, I think,"},{"time":177541,"text":"towards a single, underlying mechanism"},{"time":180089,"text":"for intelligence."},{"time":181670,"text":"In cosmology, for example,"},{"time":184216,"text":"there have been a variety of\ndifferent threads of evidence"},{"time":186963,"text":"that our universe appears to be finely tuned"},{"time":190370,"text":"for the development of intelligence,"},{"time":192523,"text":"and, in particular, for the development"},{"time":194912,"text":"of universal states"},{"time":196798,"text":"that maximize the diversity of possible futures."},{"time":200896,"text":"In game play, for example, in Go --"},{"time":203240,"text":"everyone remembers in 1997"},{"time":206265,"text":"when IBM's Deep Blue beat \nGarry Kasparov at chess --"},{"time":210216,"text":"fewer people are aware"},{"time":211739,"text":"that in the past 10 years or so,"},{"time":213757,"text":"the game of Go,"},{"time":214955,"text":"arguably a much more challenging game"},{"time":216911,"text":"because it has a much higher branching factor,"},{"time":219336,"text":"has also started to succumb"},{"time":221038,"text":"to computer game players"},{"time":222903,"text":"for the same reason:"},{"time":224476,"text":"the best techniques right now\nfor computers playing Go"},{"time":227276,"text":"are techniques that try to maximize future options"},{"time":230972,"text":"during game play."},{"time":232986,"text":"Finally, in robotic motion planning,"},{"time":236567,"text":"there have been a variety of recent techniques"},{"time":238749,"text":"that have tried to take advantage"},{"time":240651,"text":"of abilities of robots to maximize"},{"time":243797,"text":"future freedom of action"},{"time":245303,"text":"in order to accomplish complex tasks."},{"time":248400,"text":"And so, taking all of these different threads"},{"time":250755,"text":"and putting them together,"},{"time":252377,"text":"I asked, starting several years ago,"},{"time":255017,"text":"is there an underlying mechanism for intelligence"},{"time":257867,"text":"that we can factor out"},{"time":259540,"text":"of all of these different threads?"},{"time":261314,"text":"Is there a single equation for intelligence?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265907,"text":"And the answer, I believe, is yes.\n[\"F = T ∇ Sτ\"]"},{"time":269278,"text":"What you're seeing is probably"},{"time":271191,"text":"the closest equivalent to an E = mc²"},{"time":274485,"text":"for intelligence that I've seen."},{"time":277315,"text":"So what you're seeing here"},{"time":279017,"text":"is a statement of correspondence"},{"time":281686,"text":"that intelligence is a force, F,"},{"time":286121,"text":"that acts so as to maximize future freedom of action."},{"time":290771,"text":"It acts to maximize future freedom of action,"},{"time":293146,"text":"or keep options open,"},{"time":294774,"text":"with some strength T,"},{"time":296999,"text":"with the diversity of possible accessible futures, S,"},{"time":301776,"text":"up to some future time horizon, tau."},{"time":304326,"text":"In short, intelligence doesn't like to get trapped."},{"time":307535,"text":"Intelligence tries to maximize\nfuture freedom of action"},{"time":310590,"text":"and keep options open."},{"time":313263,"text":"And so, given this one equation,"},{"time":315696,"text":"it's natural to ask, so what can you do with this?"},{"time":318228,"text":"How predictive is it?"},{"time":319579,"text":"Does it predict human-level intelligence?"},{"time":321714,"text":"Does it predict artificial intelligence?"},{"time":324532,"text":"So I'm going to show you now a video"},{"time":326574,"text":"that will, I think, demonstrate"},{"time":329994,"text":"some of the amazing applications"},{"time":332282,"text":"of just this single equation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334601,"text":"(Video) Narrator: Recent research in cosmology"},{"time":336580,"text":"has suggested that universes that produce"},{"time":338627,"text":"more disorder, or \"entropy,\" over their lifetimes"},{"time":342108,"text":"should tend to have more favorable conditions"},{"time":344586,"text":"for the existence of intelligent\nbeings such as ourselves."},{"time":347602,"text":"But what if that tentative cosmological connection"},{"time":350176,"text":"between entropy and intelligence"},{"time":352019,"text":"hints at a deeper relationship?"},{"time":353790,"text":"What if intelligent behavior doesn't just correlate"},{"time":356354,"text":"with the production of long-term entropy,"},{"time":358198,"text":"but actually emerges directly from it?"},{"time":360516,"text":"To find out, we developed a software engine"},{"time":362922,"text":"called Entropica, designed to maximize"},{"time":365425,"text":"the production of long-term entropy"},{"time":367193,"text":"of any system that it finds itself in."},{"time":369769,"text":"Amazingly, Entropica was able to pass"},{"time":371924,"text":"multiple animal intelligence\ntests, play human games,"},{"time":375380,"text":"and even earn money trading stocks,"},{"time":377526,"text":"all without being instructed to do so."},{"time":379637,"text":"Here are some examples of Entropica in action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382155,"text":"Just like a human standing\nupright without falling over,"},{"time":385360,"text":"here we see Entropica"},{"time":386590,"text":"automatically balancing a pole using a cart."},{"time":389475,"text":"This behavior is remarkable in part"},{"time":391487,"text":"because we never gave Entropica a goal."},{"time":393818,"text":"It simply decided on its own to balance the pole."},{"time":396975,"text":"This balancing ability will have appliactions"},{"time":399107,"text":"for humanoid robotics"},{"time":400504,"text":"and human assistive technologies."},{"time":403019,"text":"Just as some animals can use objects"},{"time":405020,"text":"in their environments as tools"},{"time":406462,"text":"to reach into narrow spaces,"},{"time":408449,"text":"here we see that Entropica,"},{"time":410331,"text":"again on its own initiative,"},{"time":412169,"text":"was able to move a large\ndisk representing an animal"},{"time":415079,"text":"around so as to cause a small disk,"},{"time":417424,"text":"representing a tool, to reach into a confined space"},{"time":420195,"text":"holding a third disk"},{"time":421732,"text":"and release the third disk\nfrom its initially fixed position."},{"time":424704,"text":"This tool use ability will have applications"},{"time":426893,"text":"for smart manufacturing and agriculture."},{"time":429252,"text":"In addition, just as some other animals"},{"time":431196,"text":"are able to cooperate by pulling\nopposite ends of a rope"},{"time":433892,"text":"at the same time to release food,"},{"time":435945,"text":"here we see that Entropica is able to accomplish"},{"time":438240,"text":"a model version of that task."},{"time":440228,"text":"This cooperative ability has interesting implications"},{"time":442750,"text":"for economic planning and a variety of other fields."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446185,"text":"Entropica is broadly applicable"},{"time":448256,"text":"to a variety of domains."},{"time":450199,"text":"For example, here we see it successfully"},{"time":452641,"text":"playing a game of pong against itself,"},{"time":455200,"text":"illustrating its potential for gaming."},{"time":457543,"text":"Here we see Entropica orchestrating"},{"time":459462,"text":"new connections on a social network"},{"time":461301,"text":"where friends are constantly falling out of touch"},{"time":464061,"text":"and successfully keeping\nthe network well connected."},{"time":466917,"text":"This same network orchestration ability"},{"time":469215,"text":"also has applications in health care,"},{"time":471543,"text":"energy, and intelligence."},{"time":474775,"text":"Here we see Entropica directing the paths"},{"time":476860,"text":"of a fleet of ships,"},{"time":478346,"text":"successfully discovering and\nutilizing the Panama Canal"},{"time":481521,"text":"to globally extend its reach from the Atlantic"},{"time":483979,"text":"to the Pacific."},{"time":485508,"text":"By the same token, Entropica"},{"time":487235,"text":"is broadly applicable to problems"},{"time":488855,"text":"in autonomous defense, logistics and transportation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494173,"text":"Finally, here we see Entropica"},{"time":496203,"text":"spontaneously discovering and executing"},{"time":498926,"text":"a buy-low, sell-high strategy"},{"time":500993,"text":"on a simulated range traded stock,"},{"time":503171,"text":"successfully growing assets under management"},{"time":505502,"text":"exponentially."},{"time":506926,"text":"This risk management ability"},{"time":508234,"text":"will have broad applications in finance"},{"time":510721,"text":"and insurance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514049,"text":"Alex Wissner-Gross: So what you've just seen"},{"time":516140,"text":"is that a variety of signature human intelligent"},{"time":520532,"text":"cognitive behaviors"},{"time":522289,"text":"such as tool use and walking upright"},{"time":525120,"text":"and social cooperation"},{"time":527149,"text":"all follow from a single equation,"},{"time":530121,"text":"which drives a system"},{"time":532053,"text":"to maximize its future freedom of action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535964,"text":"Now, there's a profound irony here."},{"time":538971,"text":"Going back to the beginning"},{"time":540995,"text":"of the usage of the term robot,"},{"time":544268,"text":"the play \"RUR,\""},{"time":547171,"text":"there was always a concept"},{"time":549406,"text":"that if we developed machine intelligence,"},{"time":552632,"text":"there would be a cybernetic revolt."},{"time":555659,"text":"The machines would rise up against us."},{"time":559210,"text":"One major consequence of this work"},{"time":561529,"text":"is that maybe all of these decades,"},{"time":564298,"text":"we've had the whole concept of cybernetic revolt"},{"time":567274,"text":"in reverse."},{"time":569285,"text":"It's not that machines first become intelligent"},{"time":572564,"text":"and then megalomaniacal"},{"time":574579,"text":"and try to take over the world."},{"time":576803,"text":"It's quite the opposite,"},{"time":578237,"text":"that the urge to take control"},{"time":581143,"text":"of all possible futures"},{"time":583404,"text":"is a more fundamental principle"},{"time":585522,"text":"than that of intelligence,"},{"time":586885,"text":"that general intelligence may in fact emerge"},{"time":590585,"text":"directly from this sort of control-grabbing,"},{"time":594144,"text":"rather than vice versa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598329,"text":"Another important consequence is goal seeking."},{"time":602098,"text":"I'm often asked, how does the ability to seek goals"},{"time":606458,"text":"follow from this sort of framework?"},{"time":608078,"text":"And the answer is, the ability to seek goals"},{"time":611106,"text":"will follow directly from this"},{"time":612988,"text":"in the following sense:"},{"time":614822,"text":"just like you would travel through a tunnel,"},{"time":617687,"text":"a bottleneck in your future path space,"},{"time":620192,"text":"in order to achieve many other"},{"time":622063,"text":"diverse objectives later on,"},{"time":624084,"text":"or just like you would invest"},{"time":626456,"text":"in a financial security,"},{"time":628243,"text":"reducing your short-term liquidity"},{"time":630480,"text":"in order to increase your wealth over the long term,"},{"time":632880,"text":"goal seeking emerges directly"},{"time":635217,"text":"from a long-term drive"},{"time":636946,"text":"to increase future freedom of action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640983,"text":"Finally, Richard Feynman, famous physicist,"},{"time":644511,"text":"once wrote that if human civilization were destroyed"},{"time":648183,"text":"and you could pass only a single concept"},{"time":650076,"text":"on to our descendants"},{"time":651447,"text":"to help them rebuild civilization,"},{"time":653754,"text":"that concept should be"},{"time":655440,"text":"that all matter around us"},{"time":657292,"text":"is made out of tiny elements"},{"time":659615,"text":"that attract each other when they're far apart"},{"time":662123,"text":"but repel each other when they're close together."},{"time":665453,"text":"My equivalent of that statement"},{"time":667234,"text":"to pass on to descendants"},{"time":668502,"text":"to help them build artificial intelligences"},{"time":671214,"text":"or to help them understand human intelligence,"},{"time":674163,"text":"is the following:"},{"time":675430,"text":"Intelligence should be viewed"},{"time":677483,"text":"as a physical process"},{"time":678896,"text":"that tries to maximize future freedom of action"},{"time":681861,"text":"and avoid constraints in its own future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685477,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686835,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}